<section id="manifesto" class="py-24 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h2
      class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-primary dark:text-primary-dark text-center sm:text-4xl mb-12"
    >
      Our Manifesto
    </h2>
    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert mx-auto">
      <p
        class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-secondary dark:text-secondary-dark mb-8"
      >
        Event Destinations represents a fundamental shift in how we think about
        and implement event routing in modern data architectures. In today's
        data-driven world, organizations face increasing complexity in managing
        and routing events across diverse systems and platforms. The lack of
        standardization has led to fragmented implementations, increased
        maintenance overhead, and reduced interoperability.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg text-secondary dark:text-secondary-dark mb-8">
        We believe that event routing should be:
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
          <h3
            class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary dark:text-primary-dark mb-3"
          >
            1. Standardized
          </h3>
          <p class="text-secondary dark:text-secondary-dark">
            A manifesto that provides a clear, consistent way to define event
            destinations across different platforms and technologies. This
            standardization enables better tooling, documentation, and community
            support.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
          <h3
            class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary dark:text-primary-dark mb-3"
          >
            2. Interoperable
          </h3>
          <p class="text-secondary dark:text-secondary-dark">
            Event destinations should work seamlessly across different systems
            and platforms. Implementation details should be abstracted away,
            allowing developers to focus on business logic rather than
            integration specifics.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
          <h3
            class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary dark:text-primary-dark mb-3"
          >
            3. Developer-First
          </h3>
          <p class="text-secondary dark:text-secondary-dark">
            The manifesto prioritizes developer experience, providing clear
            interfaces, comprehensive documentation, and intuitive abstractions
            that make it easy to implement and maintain event routing systems.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
          <h3
            class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary dark:text-primary-dark mb-3"
          >
            4. Extensible
          </h3>
          <p class="text-secondary dark:text-secondary-dark">
            While providing standardization, the manifesto remains flexible
            enough to accommodate diverse use cases and future requirements.
            Extensions and custom implementations should be possible without
            breaking the core manifesto.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
          <h3
            class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary dark:text-primary-dark mb-3"
          >
            5. Performance-Oriented
          </h3>
          <p class="text-secondary dark:text-secondary-dark">
            The design considers performance implications, enabling efficient
            event routing at scale while maintaining reliability and
            consistency.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg text-secondary dark:text-secondary-dark mt-8 mb-4">
        By adhering to these principles, Event Destinations aims to solve the
        following challenges:
      </p>

      <ul
        class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-secondary dark:text-secondary-dark mb-8"
      >
        <li>Reduce implementation complexity and maintenance overhead</li>
        <li>Enable better tooling and ecosystem development</li>
        <li>Improve system interoperability and portability</li>
        <li>Foster community collaboration and knowledge sharing</li>
        <li>
          Accelerate development and innovation in event-driven architectures
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-lg text-secondary dark:text-secondary-dark">
        We invite the community to join us in this journey towards better event
        routing. Together, we can build a more connected, efficient, and
        standardized approach to handling events in modern data stacks.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
